Let me start by saying I'm no expert when it comes to snowballs. I'm not a local, but I think the difference between regular shaved ice/snowcones and New Orleans-style snowballs is that these often have more to them. Instead of just being shaved ice, they can put ice cream, condensed milk, or some other interesting filling inside. The New Orleans snowball just seems more elaborate.  Anyhow, this place Sno-La Snowballs is pretty good and serves up a wide variety. I tried the Oreo Cheesecake, which had some cheesecake flavored ice cream in the middle, whipped cream, and some crumbled oreo. I got a small, which was honestly huge and more than I could eat. I'd definitely like to return next trip.  Side-note: I always hear snowballs are a summer thing, but this place was good to go right around Halloween. So, no seasonal issues here.

I used to really like this place. Some of the newer people i have seen working in there lately have bad attitudes. The nerve to be looking for a tip though. The last two visits my family and I have had here were not pleasant. The time before last, we went in on a Sunday and they gave both me and my daughter sno-balls with clear ice on the inside. That is just how little syrup they put on the snow-balls. After taking only a few scoops we noticed this and brought them back in for them to correct this. Either they are trying to save on syrup or the person making the son-balls had no idea what they were doing.  On the last visit, my family and i went back in and placed our orders - 5 sno-balls. Our sno-balls were placed on the counter by this one girl with no notification by any of the staff that they were ready. After watching them having placed two sno-balls on the counter and then the third, I walked up and asked if they were ours and was told they were. I realized soon after that the sno-balls did not look what we were used to because they had no condensed milk. I asked if they would add condensed milk and was told by a girl behind the counter with an attitude saying "well you need to ask for it". Well that's interesting because usually its the cashier that would verify with us whether or not we wanted condensed milk and we would always get it. I explained to her that we always got condensed milk on our sno-balls and the girl proceeded to add condense milk to the sno-balls. She puts the sno-balls on the counter after doing so and she put so much condensed milk on those sno-balls that the condensed milk was literally pouring over the rim of the sno-balls. I was so disgusted. Sno-balls were a complete mess. It took us maybe 5 minutes to get the excess condensed milk from over flowing from the cups. Then to top it off, the sno-balls didn't even taste good. In the process of getting the sno-balls and leaving, I could hear the girl calling other customers' names notfiying them that their sno-balls were ready so that would indicate to me that their policy has not changed in that regard. For whatever reason, she chose not to notify me and my family of our sno-balls being ready, but notified the other people placing their orders before and after us that their sno-balls were ready. This place has been truly a disappointment to me and my family. Business owners should remember and require that their employees understand the importance of good customer service because people have choices in where they spend their money. Too many sno-ball stands in the GNO to have to settle on any one place really. A good experience and you tell one person. A bad experience and you tell the world.
